# 🤖 Machine Learning Model

## Objective

Predict whether a customer is likely to churn based on demographic, contract, and service usage data.

---

## Models Evaluated

### Logistic Regression

Used as baseline model.

### Random Forest Classifier

Selected as final model due to better performance and ability to capture complex patterns.

---

# ⚙️ Model Training Pipeline

## Train-Test Split

* Training Data: 80%
* Testing Data: 20%

---

## Feature Scaling

Applied StandardScaler on numerical features:

* Age
* Tenure
* Monthly Charges
* Total Charges

---

## Model Training

Random Forest Classifier:

* 100 Estimators
* Balanced Class Weights
* Tuned Threshold for Improved Recall

---

# 📈 Model Evaluation

Evaluation Metrics:

### Accuracy

Measures overall correctness.

### Precision

Measures quality of churn predictions.

### Recall

Measures ability to detect actual churners.

### F1 Score

Balance between precision and recall.

### Confusion Matrix

Detailed prediction breakdown.

---

## Final Model Performance

| Metric    | Score |
| --------- | ----- |
| Accuracy  | ~67%  |
| Recall    | ~75%  |
| Precision | ~51%  |
| F1 Score  | ~61%  |

### Business Interpretation

The model prioritizes recall to identify more customers likely to churn, enabling proactive retention efforts.

---

# 🚨 Customer Risk Segmentation

Predicted customers are categorized into:

### 🟢 Low Risk

Churn Probability < 40%

### 🟡 Medium Risk

Churn Probability 40–70%

### 🔴 High Risk

Churn Probability > 70%

